      "<b>Part 1: Introduction to Zambia</b>:<br><br>Zambia is a landlocked country located in Southern Africa, known for its rich natural resources, diverse wildlife, and vibrant cultures.<br><br>Capital City: Lusaka<br>Major Landmarks: Victoria Falls, Lake Tanganyika, and the Zambezi River.<br>Size: Zambia covers an area of approximately 752,612 square kilometers.<br><br>Discussion:<br>Begin the lesson by asking students if they know where Zambia is located or if they have heard of it before. Show a map of Africa, highlighting Zambia’s position.",
